      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's a good start but maybe a bit too generic. can you make it sound a little more personal? like, i want them to feel like we actually valued the conversation we had, rather than just feeling like they got a template. maybe add a line about how much we enjoyed their perspective on scalability?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to personally reach out and thank you for the time and effort you invested in the interview process for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We truly appreciated the depth of knowledge and passion you brought to the table, especially your insights on system design and your perspective on scalability. It was a pleasure discussing your ideas and learning from your experiences.\n\nAfter careful deliberation, we have made the difficult decision to move forward with another candidate whose experience with our specific cloud stack aligns more closely with our immediate needs. This decision was not an easy one, and we were genuinely impressed by your expertise and the positive cultural fit you demonstrated during our conversations.\n\nWe understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that we value the opportunity to have worked with you. We believe you have a bright future ahead, and we wish you all the best in your continued professional journey.\n\nThank you once again for your interest in [Company Name] and for sharing your valuable insights with us. We hope to stay in touch and possibly collaborate in the future.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n[Your Name]  \n[Your Position]  \n[Company",
      "source": "target",
